ces revenue us billion  net income us million  number of employees  website wwwpolycomcom polycom is an american multinational corporation that develops video voice and content collaboration and communication technology the firm employs approximately  employees and had annual revenues of approximately  billion in  it is the largest pureplay collaboration company in its industry the company also licenses h video codecs siren codecs session initiation protocol native p highdefinition cameras and displays native p and p highdefinition encodingdecoding lowlatency architecture and low bandwidth utilization wideband advanced audio coding with low delay aacld multichannel spatial audio with echo cancellation and interference filters to eliminate feedback from mobile devices and interoperation with legacy video conferencing in july  it was announced that the company was being taken private by private equity firm siris capital group contents  history  company history  acquisitions  company product trajectory  polycom video  polycom audio and voice  references  external links historyedit company historyedit polycom was cofounded in  by brian l hinman and jeffrey rodman who were colleagues at picturetel corp in  telecommunications executive mary mcdowell was named as its chief executive officer acquisitionsedit polycoms development occurred both by internal means and by the acquisition of other companies acquisition date company acquired company business reference january  viavideo communications inc appliancebased video communications systems  december  atlas communications engines inc integrated access device and dsl routers  february  accord networks provider of nextgeneration richmedia network products  april  circa communications ip telephony products  october  picturetel pcbased video communications systems  december  aspi digital installed voice systems  june  meetu web collaboration software  january  vcas software from agt video scheduling and management software january  voyant technologies voice conferencing and collaboration network solutions  august  dst media chinabased video networking company  january  destiny conferencing immersive telepresence  march  spectralink and kirk telecom workplace wireless telephony  march  accordent technologies rich media streaming and management solutions  october  vivu inc video collaboration software  note   june  – hp and polycom announced they have entered into a definitive agreement under which polycom will acquire the assets of hps visual collaboration hpvc business including the halo products and managed services business of hpvc on april   polycom announced that rival mitel networks would purchase them for  billion mitel a smaller company based in ottawa canada pays a lower tax rate the acquisition may be an example of tax inversion where a smaller company purchases a larger company in order to provide the combined larger corporate entity with the tax benefits of the smaller companys location in july  the mitel deal was scrapped and instead the company took an allcash offer from ny citybased private equity firm siris capital group company product trajectoryedit this section does not cite any sources please help improve this section by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed november  learn how and when to remove this template message polycoms first products to market were audio conferencing speakerphones soon after the company added content sharing video conferencing and video network and bridging products polycom videoedit polycom vsx  unit with dual displays polycom entered the video conferencing market in  polycom introduced the viewstation product line which included models with embedded multipoint capabilities content sharing capabilities and support for the emerging h ip network protocol in  polycom introduced a personal desktop video conferencing appliance called viavideo the compact device was essentially a web cam with inboard processing capabilities to offset the compute limitations of most desktop and laptop computers at the time as computer processing power increased polycom transitioned the desktop solution to a softwarebased client called polycom pvx in february  polycom acquired accord networks which offered the mgc line in october  it acquired picturetel polycom digital tabletop microphone with mute button in  polycom introduced its first high definition video conferencing system soon after it announced the polycom realpresence experience rpx immersive telepresence solution a roomwithinaroom telepresence environment based on the design by destiny conferencing formerly telesuites which polycom acquired  in january  in february  the firm introduced a new bridge platform called rmx  designed to support high definition and telepresence applications it also expanded its telepresence and hd video product lines in  with the polycom telepresence experience solutions and new executive desktop solutions expanded its line of roombased conference rooms in  polycom delivered the polycom converged management application cma a video network and system management application for provisioning and managing video networks the cma includes an application for broadscale desktop video called cma desktop later that year the firm introduced the distributed media application dma  a networkbased application that manages and distributes multipoint video calls within an enterprise network environment toward the end of  polycom also announced its plans to support higher resolution – p and p at  frames per second same frame rate as tv – across its visual communication product line endpoints telepresence solutions and infrastructure solutions during  the firm introduced a new immersive telepresence solution the polycom open telepresence experience otx  providing collaboration including p using half the bandwidth of other comparable systems polycom audio and voiceedit polycom soundstation ip  sip conference phone t